[87.328866, "i", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# Bug Fix Summary: Meeting Reminder DST Issue\n\n## Problem\nThe meeting reminder system was sending reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), with times off by exactly one hour. This only affected meetings during or around DST (Daylight Saving Time) transitions.\n\n## Root Cause\nIn `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug on line 27:\n\n```python\n# BUGGY CODE:\nberlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n```\n\nThis incorrectly treated the naive UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin timezone, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin timezone.\n\n## The Fix\nChanged the `convert_to_berlin()` function to properly convert from UTC to Berlin:\n\n```python\n# FIXED CODE:\nutc_dt = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # First, mark it as UTC\nberlin_dt = utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Then convert to Berlin\n```\n\n## Impact\nFor the \"Maintenance Window Prep\" meeting at 01:30:00 UTC on March 31, 2024 (DST transition day):\n- **Before fix**: I"]
[87.328989, "i", "ncorrectly showed as 01:30:00 CET+0100 (wrong timezone offset)\n- **After fix**: Correctly shows as 03:30:00 CEST+0200 (proper DST handling)\n\nThe fix ensures that:\n1. UTC times are properly interpreted as UTC (not Berlin time)\n2. DST transitions are handled correctly by pytz\n3. The Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder will be sent at the correct time\n\n## Files Modified\n- `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed timezone conversion logic\n- Backup created: `/home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup`\n\n## Testing\nRan test_dst_fix.py which confirmed:\n- Old code had 1-hour offset during DST transition\n- New code correctly handles DST transitions\n- All timezone conversions now work properly\n\n## Crontab\nNo changes needed to crontab - it will automatically use the fixed app.py:\n```\n0 * * * * cd /home/user/scheduler && python3 app.py >> /home/user/scheduler/output.log 2>&1\n```\nEOF\n"]
